When using a `List<String>` Widget, using `list.getItems().add("some string");` causes the item to display, but not be selectable.

```
    final List<String> list = new List<String>(game.skin);
    list.getItems().add("Abc");
    list.getItems().add("Def");
    list.getItems().add("GHI");
    list.getItems().add("JKL");
    list.getItems().add("MNO");
    list.addListener(new ChangeListener() {
        @Override
        public void changed(ChangeEvent event, Actor actor) {
            Gdx.app.log("Menu", list.getSelected());
        }
    });
    table.add(list);
```

Using `setItems` however, works as expected:

```
    final List<String> list = new List<String>(skin);
    list.setItems("Abc", "Def", "GHI", "JKL");
    list.addListener(new ChangeListener() {
        @Override
        public void changed(ChangeEvent event, Actor actor) {
            Gdx.app.log("Menu", list.getSelected());
        }
    });
    table.add(list);
```

Is this a bug, or is it not intended to be able to add items dynamically in this way? (If it is not, then why does it display them?)

I'm using libGDX 1.5.3

